children.description: How to test API endpoints with Clobbr

children.value: Our devs at Setapp love this app for a reason. Meet Clobbr, a powerful yet easy-to-use tool to load- and speed-test your API endpoints. Clobbr stores your data locally, doesn't require an account, and looks delightful. What more could we ask for?

children.name: Clobbr Load test API endpoints Clobbr 90 % Mac

children.value: Whether you're testing REST, GraphQL, or cloud functions, Clobbr will do the job. Simply enter a URL, tweak the options, and start testing. You can quickly switch between parallel and sequence testing, change the HTTP method, set timeouts and the number of iterations.

Configuring headers for your request is just as easy. Once you've entered a URL, click the Configure button and jump to the Headers tab. Besides adding everything manually, you can use scripts for dynamic headers.
Need to send any data with your request? Go to the Payload tab and use Clobbr's built-in JSON editor. Autocomplete, validation, and syntax highlighting are here for you.
Catch any concurrency and performance issues early on with Clobb's detailed analytics. Click "History & analysis" to dive into key metrics and see how they changed over time.
Want to highlight potential issues to your team? Click the Share button to get a link with your test results chart. All your data stays locally, and you can also hide the request URL.
Hope this guide will help you solve tasks faster, and enjoy solving them, too! Check out more guides picked for you below.
